condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section I D. 5Merger of Alat and Karakul district vodokanals | Description :The Recipient shall,by not later than January 15, 2013, submit to the Association the decree for the restructuring of the Project Implementing Entitytoabsorb the assets and operations of the water supply service providers at the district level in Alat and Karakul. | Due Date:15-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section IA.1, Interagency Council for Cooperation | Description :The Recipient shall maintain theInteragency Council for Cooperation (ICC) until completion of the Project with terms of reference satisfactory to IDA. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section IA.2, Project Coordination Unit | Description :Recipient shall maintain the ProjectCoordination Unit (PCU) within Uzkommunkhizmat including representatives at the Project Implementing Entity until completion of theProject with staff, resources and terms of reference satisfactory to IDA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section ID.4, Disposal facility | Description :GOU shall cause the PIE to construct a disposalfacility in the vicinity of Dvoinik, in accordance with the safety standards and technical requirements agreed with IDA, for thewater treatment sludge and sediments generated by the Project, by not later than November 15, 2013. The Recipient shall notcommence construction of a new water treatment plant until such facility is completed (FA excerpt) | Due Date :15-Nov-2013

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2 Section II B. 5 , Debt service ratio | Description :GOU shall take all measures to ensure PIEshall not incur any debt unless a reasonable forecast of revenues and expenditures shows that the estimated net revenues for eachfiscal year during the term of the debt to be incurred is at least 1.2 time its estimated debt service requirement in such year onall debt of the PIE, including the debt to be incurred (FA excerpt). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :FA Schedule 2, Section II. B. 4, Working Ratio | Description :GOU shall take all measures to ensure PIEmaintains for the years 2013 and 2014 a ratio of total cash operating expenses to totalcash operating revenues not higher than 1.0and a ratio not higher than 0.9 for the remaining years, and to enable the PIE to collect effectively all operating revenuesrelated to its operations (FA excerpt). | Frequency :Yearly
